Squares $ABCD$ and $EFGH$ are equal in area.  Vertices $B$, $E$, $C$, and $H$ lie on the same line.  Diagonal $AC$ is extended to $J$, the midpoint of $GH$.  What is the fraction of the two squares that is shaded? [asy]
fill((0,4)--(4,4)--(4,0)--cycle,gray);
fill((4,0)--(6,0)--(6,-2)--cycle,gray);
draw((0,0)--(4,0)--(4,4)--(0,4)--cycle,linewidth(1));
draw((2,0)--(6,0)--(6,-4)--(2,-4)--cycle,linewidth(1));
draw((0,4)--(6,-2),linewidth(1));
label("$A$",(0,4),NW);
label("$B$",(0,0),W);
label("$C$",(4,0),NE);
label("$D$",(4,4),NE);
label("$E$",(2,0),SW);
label("$F$",(2,-4),SW);
label("$G$",(6,-4),SE);
label("$H$",(6,0),E);
label("$J$",(6,-2),E);
[/asy]

A right pyramid has a square base that measures 10 cm on each side. Its peak is 12 cm above the center of its base. What is the sum of the lengths of the pyramid's eight edges? Express your answer to the nearest whole number.

[asy]
size(150);
draw((0,0)--(3,3)--(13,3)--(10,0)--cycle,linewidth(1));
draw((0,0)--(6.5,15)--(3,3),linewidth(1));
draw((13,3)--(6.5,15)--(10,0),linewidth(1));
draw((6.5,15)--(6.5,1.5),linewidth(1));
label("12",(6.5,5),E);

draw((6.6,15)..(6.7,14.9)..(6.8,14.7)--(6.8,5.3)..(6.9,5.2)..(7,5)..(6.9,4.8)..(6.8,4.7)--(6.8,1.8)..(6.7,1.6)..(6.6,1.5),linewidth(.7));

[/asy]
